---
import IcomatLayout from "@/layouts/Icomat.astro";
---

<IcomatLayout meta={{ title: "Home", description: "DFW Sikh Shooters — Tyar Bar Tyar" }}>
	<!-- Hero: full-viewport cinematic image (ICOMAT solutions hero) -->
	<section class="ic-hero">
		<div class="ic-hero__media">
			<img
				src="/assets/images/industrial/hero-rifle.jpg"
				alt="Modern tactical platform — industrial studio presentation"
				width="1920"
				height="1080"
				fetchpriority="high"
			/>
		</div>
		<div class="ic-hero__spotlight" aria-hidden="true"></div>
	</section>

	<!-- Hero text: split headline + intro (ICOMAT HeroText) -->
	<section class="ic-hero-text ic-reveal">
		<div>
			<h1>ਵਾਹਿਗੁਰੂ ਜੀ ਕਾ ਖਾਲਸਾ । ਵਾਹਿਗੁਰੂ ਜੀ ਕੀ ਫਤਹਿ ।</h1>
			<p class="ic-hero-text__sub" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Waheguru Ji Ka Khalsa, Waheguru Ji Ki Fateh</p>
		</div>
		<p class="ic-hero-text__sub">
			In Sikhi, the sword (ਕ੍ਰਿਪਾਨ) holds deep spiritual and temporal significance. It represents divine power,
			dignity, self-respect, and the Sikh commitment to defend the defenseless. As one of the Five Ks, it serves as a
			constant reminder of our responsibility to uphold justice and righteousness.
		</p>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 100; --space-desktop: 200"></div>

	<!-- Two column: Prove Fast / process copy -->
	<section class="ic-two-col ic-two-col--light ic-reveal">
		<div class="ic-two-col__inner">
			<div class="ic-two-col__left">
				<h3>
					Contemporary platforms.<br />
					Ancestral discipline.<br />
					Unchanged principles.
				</h3>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-two-col__right">
				<p>
					In the modern era, the Sikh principle of being "Tyar Bar Tyar" (Ready at all times) remains as relevant as
					ever. Here's why weapons training continues to be an essential part of the Sikh way of life:
				</p>
				<br />
				<p>
					History has shown that evil does not rest, and the only way to prevent suffering at the hands of tyrants is to
					maintain the highest level of defensive capability legally permitted. This includes modern sporting rifles and
					similar platforms - if those who wish harm can access such tools, it is our duty to be equally prepared to
					defend the innocent.
				</p>
				<br />
				<p>
					Remember that Guru Gobind Singh Ji equipped the Khalsa with the most advanced arms available in their time.
					Today, we honor that tradition by maintaining proficiency with modern defensive tools while upholding the same
					principles of restraint, discipline, and righteousness.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 100; --space-desktop: 200"></div>

	<!-- Video / cinematic section -->
	<section class="ic-video-section ic-reveal">
		<div class="ic-video-section__media">
			<img
				src="/assets/images/industrial/section-tactical.jpg"
				alt="Tactical precision — field operations"
				width="1920"
				height="1080"
				loading="lazy"
			/>
		</div>
		<div class="ic-video-section__overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
		<p class="ic-video-section__title">Shastar Vidya &amp; Modern Readiness</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Sticky center heading: One System. Three Stages. -->
	<section class="ic-center-heading">
		<div class="ic-center-heading__sticky">
			<h2 class="ic-center-heading__ghost" aria-hidden="true">One Path. Three Pillars.</h2>
			<h2>One Path. Three Pillars.</h2>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 100; --space-desktop: 200"></div>

	<!-- Two column: system bullets -->
	<section class="ic-two-col ic-two-col--dark ic-reveal">
		<div class="ic-two-col__inner">
			<div class="ic-two-col__left">
				<h3>Our commitment is a system.</h3>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-two-col__right">
				<ul class="ic-two-col__list">
					<li>
						<strong>Religious Duty</strong>
						<span
							>Guru Gobind Singh Ji instructed Sikhs to be both Sant (Saints) and Sipahi (Warriors). This dual responsibility
							continues in the modern world.</span
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Self-Defense</strong>
						<span
							>In an increasingly uncertain world, the ability to protect oneself and others is crucial. This aligns with the
							Sikh principle of standing up against injustice.</span
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Community Protection</strong>
						<span
							>Sikhs have historically been defenders of the oppressed. Modern weapons training enables us to continue this
							sacred duty.</span
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Cultural Preservation</strong>
						<span
							>Maintaining proficiency in weapons connects us to our martial heritage and the discipline of Shastar Vidya.</span
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Mental Discipline</strong>
						<span
							>Weapons training develops focus, discipline, and mindfulness - qualities essential for both spiritual and
							worldly success.</span
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Physical Fitness</strong>
						<span
							>Regular training maintains the body as a temple, following the Sikh principle of keeping the body strong and
							capable.</span
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Responsibility</strong>
						<span
							>Learning proper weapons handling teaches responsibility, safety, and respect for tools of defense.</span
						>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Timeline: O1 O2 O3 -->
	<section class="ic-timeline ic-reveal">
		<div class="ic-timeline__intro">
			<h3>ਤਿਆਰ ਬਰ ਤਿਆਰ - Tyar Bar Tyar</h3>
			<p style="color: var(--color-gray-purple); max-width: 40rem; line-height: 1.55;">
				Preparedness as sacred duty — editorial structure, unchanged conviction.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="ic-timeline__cards">
			<article class="ic-timeline-card">
				<p class="ic-timeline-card__label">O1</p>
				<div class="ic-timeline-card__image">
					<img
						src="/assets/images/industrial/section-optics.jpg"
						alt="Precision optics — technical manufacturing aesthetic"
						loading="lazy"
					/>
				</div>
				<h4>Why — Sacred Duty</h4>
				<p>
					In the modern era, the Sikh principle of being "Tyar Bar Tyar" (Ready at all times) remains as relevant as
					ever. Weapons training is an essential part of the Sikh way of life.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="ic-timeline-card">
				<p class="ic-timeline-card__label">O2</p>
				<div class="ic-timeline-card__image">
					<img
						src="/assets/images/industrial/hero-rifle-alt.jpg"
						alt="Modern rifle platform — studio industrial presentation"
						loading="lazy"
					/>
				</div>
				<h4>How — Modern Arms</h4>
				<p>
					Just as our ancestors maintained the most effective weapons of their time, today's Sikhs have a duty to be
					properly equipped with modern defensive tools.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="ic-timeline-card">
				<p class="ic-timeline-card__label">O3</p>
				<div class="ic-timeline-card__image">
					<img
						src="/assets/images/industrial/section-precision.jpg"
						alt="Advanced manufacturing — industrial precision"
						loading="lazy"
					/>
				</div>
				<h4>About — Collective</h4>
				<p>
					We are a collective of like-minded Singhs and Kaurs from across the Dallas-Fort Worth metroplex, united by our
					dedication to maintaining the Khalsa's martial traditions.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Image pair -->
	<section class="ic-image-pair ic-reveal">
		<div class="ic-image-pair__item">
			<img src="/assets/images/industrial/hero-rifle.jpg" alt="Tactical platform" loading="lazy" />
		</div>
		<div class="ic-image-pair__item">
			<img src="/assets/images/industrial/section-tactical.jpg" alt="Field operations" loading="lazy" />
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 100; --space-desktop: 200"></div>

	<!-- Two column: Who we are -->
	<section class="ic-two-col ic-two-col--light ic-reveal">
		<div class="ic-two-col__inner">
			<div class="ic-two-col__left">
				<h3>DFW Metroplex — Training Hub</h3>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-two-col__right">
				<p>
					<strong>DFW metroplex provides complete community for Sikhs committed to martial readiness.</strong>
				</p>
				<br />
				<p>
					We are a collective of like-minded Singhs and Kaurs from across the Dallas-Fort Worth metroplex, united by our
					dedication to maintaining the Khalsa's martial traditions through modern weapons training. While we attend
					different Gurdwaras throughout DFW, we come together regularly to train, learn, and grow in our understanding of
					both traditional Shastar Vidya and contemporary defensive tools.
				</p>
				<br />
				<p>
					Our members range from experienced marksmen to beginners, but we all share a common understanding: that the
					responsibility to be armed and trained is inseparable from our Sikhi. We organize regular training sessions,
					workshops, and educational events focused on responsible firearm ownership, tactical training, and the spiritual
					aspects of being a warrior-saint in today's world.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 100; --space-desktop: 200"></div>

	<!-- Numbers -->
	<section class="ic-numbers ic-reveal">
		<h2>The Foundation</h2>
		<div class="ic-numbers__grid">
			<div class="ic-numbers__item">
				<div class="ic-numbers__label">Five Ks — Sacred articles of faith</div>
				<div class="ic-numbers__value">5K</div>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-numbers__item">
				<div class="ic-numbers__label">Guru's command — Never without arms</div>
				<div class="ic-numbers__value">1</div>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-numbers__item">
				<div class="ic-numbers__label">DFW Gurdwaras — United training community</div>
				<div class="ic-numbers__value">DFW</div>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-numbers__item">
				<div class="ic-numbers__label">Khalsa spirit — One fights many</div>
				<div class="ic-numbers__value">1:125K</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 100; --space-desktop: 200"></div>

	<!-- Two column: old world vs new -->
	<section class="ic-two-col ic-two-col--light ic-reveal">
		<div class="ic-two-col__inner">
			<div class="ic-two-col__left">
				<h3>From Complacency to Eternal Vigilance</h3>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-two-col__right">
				<ul class="ic-two-col__list">
					<li>
						<strong>The old pattern</strong>
						<span
							>No one is coming to save us. Time and again, the mouths we feed at langar have come back to bite us; no
							amount of community-building saved the Sikhs from the horrors of Partition and 1984. Sikhs can only entrust
							their protection to themselves, as commanded by the Gurus.</span
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Tyar Bar Tyar</strong>
						<span
							>Today's world demands the same vigilance our ancestors maintained. Whether facing targeted violence or
							protecting the innocent, Sikhs must maintain the highest level of preparedness. This means regular training,
							maintaining defensive capabilities, and understanding that our ability to defend ourselves and others is a
							sacred responsibility passed down through generations.</span
						>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 200; --space-desktop: 300"></div>

	<!-- Banner CTA -->
	<section class="ic-banner-cta ic-reveal">
		<h2>The peace we enjoy today is but a temporary illusion.</h2>
		<a href="/why/" class="ic-cta">
			<span>Learn More</span>
			<svg viewBox="0 0 9 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
				<path
					d="M7.65039 0.650024L7.65039 6.65002"
					stroke="currentColor"
					stroke-width="1.3"
					stroke-linecap="round"
					stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
				<path
					d="M1.65039 6.65002L7.65039 0.650024L7.65039 6.65002"
					stroke="currentColor"
					stroke-width="1.3"
					stroke-linecap="round"
					stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
			</svg>
		</a>
	</section>

	<div class="ic-space" style="--space-mobile: 100; --space-desktop: 200"></div>

	<!-- Hot links -->
	<section class="ic-hot-links ic-reveal">
		<a href="/why/" class="ic-hot-link">
			<img src="/assets/images/industrial/section-tactical.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy" />
			<span class="ic-hot-link__label">Why</span>
		</a>
		<a href="/how/" class="ic-hot-link">
			<img src="/assets/images/industrial/section-optics.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy" />
			<span class="ic-hot-link__label">How</span>
		</a>
		<a href="/about/" class="ic-hot-link">
			<img src="/assets/images/industrial/hero-rifle-alt.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy" />
			<span class="ic-hot-link__label">About</span>
		</a>
	</section>

	<!-- Gurbani quote block (from home) -->
	<section class="ic-two-col ic-two-col--dark ic-reveal" style="margin-top: 0;">
		<div class="ic-two-col__inner">
			<div class="ic-two-col__left">
				<h3>Gurbani</h3>
			</div>
			<div class="ic-two-col__right">
				<p style="font-style: italic; font-size: calc(16 * var(--vr)); line-height: 1.5;">
					"ਨਾਮੁ ਤਲਵਾਰੁ ਪੀਤੰਬਰੁ ਢਾਲਾ ॥<br />
					ਸਗਲ ਸੂਟੁ ਹਮਾਰਾ ॥"
				</p>
				<br />
				<p>
					"The Name is my sword; the Lord, my shield.<br />
					The entire body is my armor."<br />
					- Sri Guru Granth Sahib Ji (Ang 1072)
				</p>
				<br />
				<div style="max-width: 28rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
					<img
						src="/assets/images/DFWSS-2.png"
						alt="Kirpan - Sikh ceremonial sword"
						style="width: 100%; padding: 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border-radius: 4px;"
						loading="lazy"
					/>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</IcomatLayout>
